'''Beaver Falls''', is a [[waterfall]] located on Beaver Creek near the town of [[Clatskanie, Oregon|Clatskanie]] in [[Columbia County, Oregon|Columbia County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Oregon]].<ref name="Northwest Waterfall Survey">{{cite web|title=Beaver Falls Columbia County, Oregon|url=https://www.waterfallsnorthwest.com/waterfall/Beaver-Falls-4104|website=Northwest Waterfall Survey|accessdate=8 June 2017}}</ref>

== Description ==
The waterfall is formed as Beaver Creek sheets out onto a wide channel over a 40 feet shoot at high velocity into a natural amphitheater of layered [[basalt]].<ref name="Northwest Waterfall Survey" /> Beaver Falls Trail leads to Beaver Falls in {{convert|0.3|mi|km}} from a trailhead on Beaver Falls Road.<ref>{{cite web|title=Beaver Falls in Clatskanie, Oregon|url=https://www.hikespeak.com/trails/beaver-falls-hike-columbia-county-oregon/|website=hikespeak.com|publisher=Hikespeak|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>   The waterfall and trail are surrounded by [[Douglas fir]], [[Thuja plicata|western red-cedar]], [[Tsuga heterophylla|western hemlock]], and [[Acer macrophyllum|big-leaf maple]]. [[Polystichum munitum|Sword fern]], [[Mahonia aquifolium|Oregon grape]], and [[Gaultheria shallon|salal]] are very common plant life growing beneath the [[Canopy (biology)|forest canopy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Beaver Falls Hike|url=http://www.oregonhikers.org/field_guide/Beaver_Falls_Hike|website=OregonHikers.org|publisher=|accessdate=8 June 2017}}</ref> 

